{
    "id": "231",
    "title": "Altitude-Adjusted PERC Rule",
    "desc": "The Altitude-adjusted PERC Rule for Pulmonary Embolism rules out PE if no criteria are present; includes SaO₂ adjustment for altitude. ",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18272098/",
                "text": "Wolf SJ, Mccubbin TR, Nordenholz KE, Naviaux NW, Haukoos JS. Assessment of the pulmonary embolism rule-out criteria rule for evaluation of suspected pulmonary embolism in the emergency department. Am J Emerg Med. 2008;26(2):181-5."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [
            {
                "href": "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15304025",
                "text": "Kline JA, et al. Clinical criteria to prevent unnecessary diagnostic testing in emergency department patients with suspected pulmonary embolism. J Thromb Haemost 2004; 2: 1247–55."
            },
            {
                "href": "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18318689",
                "text": "Kline JA, et al. Prospective multicenter evaluation of the pulmonary embolism rule-out criteria. J Thromb Haemost 2008; 6: 772–80."
            }
        ],
        "evidence": "<p>If any of the following is/are present, PE cannot be ruled out:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Age &ge;50.</li>\n<li>HR &ge;100.</li>\n<li>O₂ sat on room air&nbsp;<strong>&lt;95%</strong> (or O₂ sat on room air&nbsp;<strong>&lt;90%&nbsp;</strong>for high altitudes*).</li>\n<li>Unilateral leg swelling.</li>\n<li>Hemoptysis.</li>\n<li>Recent trauma or surgery.</li>\n<li>Prior PE or DVT.</li>\n<li>Hormone use (oral contraceptives, hormone replacement or estrogenic hormones use in males or female patients).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>*Altitudes &gt;4000 ft.</p>",
        "facts": "",
        "estimation": [],
        "primary_complains": [
            "Chest Pain",
            "Cough",
            "Shortness of Breath"
        ],
        "disease_treated": [
            "Deep Venous Thrombosis",
            "Pulmonary Embolism"
        ],
        "logic": "var calc_output = [];\nvar calc_msg = '';\nvar mini_msg = '';\nvar yesno = '';\n\nif (altitude==0) {\n\tvar output_score = (parseInt(age) + parseInt(hr) + parseInt(lowo2) + parseInt(dvt_pe_history) + parseInt(trauma) + parseInt(hemoptysis) + parseInt(estrogen) + parseInt(leg_swelling));\n} else if (altitude==1) {\n\tvar output_score = (parseInt(age) + parseInt(hr) + parseInt(higho2) + parseInt(dvt_pe_history) + parseInt(trauma) + parseInt(hemoptysis) + parseInt(estrogen) + parseInt(leg_swelling));\n}\n\n\nif (output_score == 0) {\n\tyesno = 'Yes';\n\tcalc_msg = 'No need for further workup.<br/><br/>If no criteria are positive, PERC-Altitude Rule criteria are satisfied.';\n\tmini_msg = 'PE can be ruled out.';\n} else {\n\tyesno = 'No';\n\tcalc_msg = 'If any criteria are positive, the PERC-Altitude Rule cannot be used to rule out PE in this patient.';\n\tmini_msg = 'PE cannot be ruled out.';\n}\ncalc_output.push({\n\tname: 'mini',\n\tvalue: yesno,\n\tvalue_text: ' ',\n\tmessage: mini_msg\n});\ncalc_output.push({\n\tname: 'PERC Rule',\n\tvalue: output_score,\n\tvalue_text: 'criteria',\n\tmessage: calc_msg\n});",
